trans-unit.source: Provides a standard set of media related commands.
trans-unit.target: Fornece um conjunto padrão de comandos relacionados à mídia.

trans-unit.source: The commands in the <xref:System.Windows.Input.MediaCommands> class and commands in the other command library classes, such as <xref:System.Windows.Input.ComponentCommands> and <xref:System.Windows.Input.ApplicationCommands>, are intended to represent a set of common commands that application programmers encounter frequently.
trans-unit.target: Os comandos de <xref:System.Windows.Input.MediaCommands> classe e comandos no outro comando classes de biblioteca, tais como <xref:System.Windows.Input.ComponentCommands> e <xref:System.Windows.Input.ApplicationCommands>, serve para representar um conjunto de comandos comuns que os programadores de aplicativos com frequência encontram.

trans-unit.source: The commands only represent the instance of the <xref:System.Windows.Input.RoutedCommand> and not the implementation logic for the command.
trans-unit.target: Os comandos representam apenas a instância das <xref:System.Windows.Input.RoutedCommand> e não a lógica de implementação do comando.

trans-unit.source: The implementation logic is bound to the command via a <xref:System.Windows.UIElement.CommandBindings%2A>.
trans-unit.target: A lógica de implementação é associada ao comando por meio de um <xref:System.Windows.UIElement.CommandBindings%2A>.

trans-unit.source: For example, if the <xref:System.Windows.Input.MediaCommands.Play%2A> command is executed on a control (the command target), the logic which performs the <xref:System.Windows.Input.MediaCommands.Play%2A> command may not be provided by the command target, so the application writer will be responsible for writing the logic that determines how the command target will handle the command.
trans-unit.target: Por exemplo, se o <xref:System.Windows.Input.MediaCommands.Play%2A> comando é executado em um controle (o destino do comando), a lógica que executa o <xref:System.Windows.Input.MediaCommands.Play%2A> comando não pode ser fornecido pelo destino de comando, então o gravador de aplicativos será responsável por gravar a lógica que determina como o destino do comando tratará o comando.

trans-unit.source: Many controls do provide implementation logic for many of the commands in the command library.
trans-unit.target: Muitos controles fornecer lógica de implementação para muitos dos comandos na biblioteca de comandos.

trans-unit.source: For example, the <xref:System.Windows.Controls.TextBox> class provides logic for the <xref:System.Windows.Input.ApplicationCommands.Paste%2A> command, <xref:System.Windows.Input.ApplicationCommands.Cut%2A> command, <xref:System.Windows.Input.ApplicationCommands.Copy%2A> command, <xref:System.Windows.Input.ApplicationCommands.Undo%2A> command, and <xref:System.Windows.Input.ApplicationCommands.Redo%2A> command.
trans-unit.target: Por exemplo, o <xref:System.Windows.Controls.TextBox> classe fornece lógica para o <xref:System.Windows.Input.ApplicationCommands.Paste%2A> comando <xref:System.Windows.Input.ApplicationCommands.Cut%2A> comando, <xref:System.Windows.Input.ApplicationCommands.Copy%2A> comando, <xref:System.Windows.Input.ApplicationCommands.Undo%2A> comando, e <xref:System.Windows.Input.ApplicationCommands.Redo%2A> comando.

trans-unit.source: For more information on commands and commanding see the [Commanding Overview](~/docs/framework/wpf/advanced/commanding-overview.md).
trans-unit.target: Para obter mais informações sobre comandos e comando, consulte o [visão geral do comando](~/docs/framework/wpf/advanced/commanding-overview.md).

trans-unit.source: Gets the value that represents the Boost Base command.
trans-unit.target: Obtém o valor que representa o comando de Aumentar Base.

trans-unit.source: This command indicates the intention to toggle the bass boost on or off.
trans-unit.target: Este comando indica a intenção de alternar o aumento dos grave ativado ou desativado.

trans-unit.source: There is not necessarily an actual implementation responding to the command on any given object; in many cases the implementation in response to that command is the responsibility of the application writer.
trans-unit.target: Não há necessariamente uma implementação real responder ao comando de qualquer objeto especificado; em muitos casos, a implementação em resposta a esse comando é responsabilidade do gravador de aplicativos.
